Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.77,0:00:02.35,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.35,0:00:04.32,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran's been acting strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.32,0:00:06.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's oddly excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.88,0:00:12.87,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Curious, the old man and I decided \Nto follow Ran on her outing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.75,0:00:18.24,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran met Sonoko and Sera at a café,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.47,0:00:20.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,where they began discussing \Nsome kind of trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.34,0:00:22.30,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.05,0:00:27.17,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if we'll get to see Okita-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.66,0:00:30.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okita?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.09,0:00:33.95,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You mean that guy who's just like Kudo-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.95,0:00:34.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.12,0:00:37.26,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.76,0:00:40.94,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,he said he lives in Kyoto's Kamigyo Ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.42,0:00:42.83,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.82,0:00:45.19,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.44,0:00:49.35,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,...going to Kyoto to see Okita?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.33,0:00:55.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.12,0:00:56.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's incidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.88,0:00:59.58,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's just incidentally meeting \NOkita on her trip to Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.83,0:01:02.99,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we'll incidentally \Nrun into Shinichi-kun, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.99,0:01:04.21,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.21,0:01:07.61,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I-Incidental?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.99,0:01:10.21,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seeing me is incidental?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.38,0:01:14.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,While this was happening, we heard \Na scream from the back of the café,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.42,0:01:16.38,Daiki,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Saraie Daiki (33) \NWaiter
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.72,0:01:18.39,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}where the body of waiter Saraie \NDaiki-san was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.99,0:01:22.29,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That locker with the broken padlock...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.29,0:01:25.36,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Was that the victim's?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.36,0:01:28.94,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's Saraie-kun's locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.41,0:01:35.19,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the culprit may \Nhave been after its contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.43,0:01:43.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's been badly ransacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.63,0:01:47.93,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea what was stolen?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.93,0:01:52.04,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure. Only its \Nowner would know for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.08,0:01:57.05,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Why is this the only locker with a padlock?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.64,0:02:01.74,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,He's been using it since \Nhe started working here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.74,0:02:05.06,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,I did think he was overly cautious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.38,0:02:08.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit really smashed the padlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.37,0:02:11.06,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,How were they able to break it like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.70,0:02:20.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Time is the y-axis, and I'm the x-axis!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.02,0:02:21.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Inscribing love and cases \Nwith deductive reasoning!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.29,0:02:23.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,More than the padlocked locker,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.91,0:02:25.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the girl's trip to Kyoto \Nhas captured my interest!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.04,0:02:27.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.59,0:02:29.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.45,0:02:31.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.98,0:04:18.98,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(398,10}The High School Girl Trio's Secret Café \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.70,0:04:16.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The High School Girl Trio's \NSecret Café, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.69,0:04:25.74,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see pliers, a hammer, \Nscrewdrivers, and a spanner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.12,0:04:29.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,None of those could break \Na padlock like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.58,0:04:31.00,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.54,0:04:35.71,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The only other thing in here \Nare these screws and nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.33,0:04:46.84,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.68,0:04:55.85,Isuzu,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Naomura Isuzu (27) \NWaiter
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.03,0:04:55.85,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I remember now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.26,0:04:57.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.14,0:05:01.11,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Something Saraie-san kept \Ncarefully locked in his locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.44,0:05:03.30,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,It was his tablet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.30,0:05:06.74,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,He often typed on it while smoking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.95,0:05:09.44,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that's what was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.92,0:05:12.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What was he typing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.52,0:05:14.58,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I asked, but he never told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.02,0:05:16.25,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,It was his blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:19.84,Toshinori,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Motosu Toshinori (38) \NCustomer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.65,0:05:17.77,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}His blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.77,0:05:23.22,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}That man wrote a food blog under \Nthe handle "the Stuffed Professor."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.22,0:05:26.26,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,He made lots of posts \Ndisparaging rival restaurants.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.51,0:05:28.89,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen that blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.89,0:05:32.18,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty popular for \Nits funny writing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.18,0:05:33.88,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.31,0:05:36.52,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it's so difficult to handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.51,0:05:42.50,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,My restaurant is hard \Nup because of that blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.50,0:05:43.88,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.68,0:05:46.70,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you stopped Sonoko-kun
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.70,0:05:51.52,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,from telling him the address of \NPoirot and its delicious sandwiches.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.58,0:05:53.62,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.30,0:06:01.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you and the manager have different \Nfamily names when you're siblings?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.65,0:06:04.41,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because the manager is married?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.41,0:06:07.26,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm getting married next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.55,0:06:10.97,Tamao,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Hasunuma Tamao (40) \NManager
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.81,0:06:12.24,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}My brother's father-in-law was \Napparently a stubborn man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:14.20,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,He said he wouldn't let him \Nmarry his only daughter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.20,0:06:16.80,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,unless he took his name and \Ntook over the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.15,0:06:18.73,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,He had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.73,0:06:20.12,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.12,0:06:24.20,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,Isuzu-chan, since your family started \Nits own branch of the restaurant,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.20,0:06:27.40,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,have they not been victimized \Nby that man's blog?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.40,0:06:30.36,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. They're barely keeping the place open.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.72,0:06:33.29,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,But the restaurant is as deserted as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.29,0:06:35.53,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,They're apparently drowning in debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.11,0:06:38.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.30,0:06:41.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure that business isn't \Ngoing under because of his blog,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.27,0:06:43.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so you killed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.11,0:06:47.76,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Then I would've complained to \Nhim like Motosu-san instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.83,0:06:52.93,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I was the restaurant's poster girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.32,0:06:58.37,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea Saraie-kun was \Nrunning that kind of blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.37,0:07:01.56,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you lived with him for a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.04,0:07:05.40,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, that's irrelevant right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.73,0:07:06.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You lived together?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.89,0:07:10.32,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You were living with the victim?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.76,0:07:15.02,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah. It was five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.02,0:07:16.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's possible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.81,0:07:22.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,he was threatening to show embarrassing \Nphotos of you from when you two dated...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.37,0:07:27.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,to your fiancé unless you paid him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.54,0:07:28.84,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.20,0:07:33.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If he was causing mischief with his \Nblog, then it's all the more likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.24,0:07:36.21,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't have any money problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.21,0:07:42.06,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,He was going to become the new manager \Nafter I got married and quit my job.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.06,0:07:44.15,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,He mentioned that to me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.46,0:07:46.84,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,He said since he'd be the next manager,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.84,0:07:50.19,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have to worry about \Nmoney if I became his girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.01,0:07:56.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the culprit is the former chef.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.82,0:08:02.66,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,How did I carry this vase back here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.66,0:08:05.88,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,I returned my keys when I quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.05,0:08:12.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means you had a key once.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.48,0:08:15.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You had the opportunity to make a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.20,0:08:19.35,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,I-I told you, I dislocated my wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.32,0:08:24.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You can fake that easily by \Nwrapping yourself in bandages,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.56,0:08:27.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and make it seem like it \Nwas dislocated all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:32.69,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,Then ask the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.69,0:08:35.03,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,They should have X-rays!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.61,0:08:39.02,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.76,0:08:43.39,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,But any of them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.04,0:08:47.36,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,could've pulled off this trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.40,0:08:50.33,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.00,0:08:52.35,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.35,0:08:54.67,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think he's acting different?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.67,0:08:55.68,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.39,0:08:58.47,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Over there. Him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.04,0:09:02.22,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The brat with the glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.95,0:09:06.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Normally he interrupts with stuff like "huh?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.43,0:09:11.73,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Or "that's weird" when there's a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.45,0:09:14.10,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.50,0:09:19.18,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun seems to be \Nthinking about the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.18,0:09:21.49,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen him scowling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.32,0:09:28.84,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on? You can't figure it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.84,0:09:29.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.07,0:09:32.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.68,0:09:34.95,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I figured out the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.34,0:09:38.11,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I don't know \Nwho the culprit is yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.11,0:09:39.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.77,0:09:44.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I figured that out when \Nwe entered the changing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.50,0:09:46.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And the trick they used, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.47,0:09:47.29,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.54,0:09:51.87,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Then when you say you don't have a clue...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.87,0:09:54.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's your trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.76,0:09:58.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She said it's an unusual trip \NI'd experience when I'm older.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.65,0:10:01.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of trip is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.65,0:10:04.32,DCItalic,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're worried about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.27,0:10:07.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,An outsider?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.34,0:10:12.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying this murder was \Ncommitted by an outsider, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.61,0:10:15.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.01,0:10:18.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,B-But all three of them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.72,0:10:22.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,had motive to murder Saraie-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.75,0:10:23.51,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.17,0:10:27.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The former chef Motosu Toshinori-san
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.88,0:10:31.02,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,had his own restaurant harshly \Ncriticized on the victim's blog.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.06,0:10:38.03,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The waitress Naomura Isuzu-san \Nwas being harassed by the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.95,0:10:44.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,The manager Hasunuma Tamao-san \Nis getting married next month,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.01,0:10:48.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and it's possible her ex-boyfriend, \Nthe victim, was threatening her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.07,0:10:53.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But when the nearly 30 kilo vase that is \Nthe murder weapon is filled with water,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.89,0:10:57.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt any of them could lift it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.42,0:11:00.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And there aren't any tools here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:04.87,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,that could be used to break the \Npadlock on the victim's locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.54,0:11:07.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But, Inspector,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.02,0:11:11.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,no one else could have \Nbrought the vase back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.72,0:11:16.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This window was open when \NSaraie-san's body was discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.46,0:11:21.18,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible he opened it to smoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.18,0:11:23.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but the manager said
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.05,0:11:27.29,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,she may have forgotten to \Nconfirm that it was locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.54,0:11:30.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,If it was left open,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.17,0:11:36.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,then someone could have entered through the \Nwindow at night and carried the vase here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.46,0:11:41.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,They could've seen Saraie-san smoking \Nwith the window open from outside,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.05,0:11:42.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,entered through the service entrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.51,0:11:47.10,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,and clubbed him to death using the vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.18,0:11:53.14,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,An incredibly strong someone who \Ncould swing a water-filled vase
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.14,0:11:56.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,weighing over 40 kilos and smash the padlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.92,0:11:58.69,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's a decoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.95,0:11:59.90,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.36,0:12:03.45,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt the culprit was \Nparticularly strong at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.10,0:12:05.24,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.87,0:12:10.20,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.32,0:12:14.33,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.84,0:12:17.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I got them, Mori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.02,0:12:19.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,A padlock and two spanners.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.58,0:12:23.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? I didn't ask you to buy those.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.61,0:12:26.53,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What? But Sera-san said...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.00,0:12:28.72,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.40,0:12:35.44,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you how to break a padlock \Nwith hardly any force at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.12,0:12:40.02,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and club a man to death using a heavy vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.33,0:12:49.08,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,First, the padlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.38,0:12:53.64,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,There was a toolbox inside \Nthose drawers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.71,0:12:58.08,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.45,0:13:03.09,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,And inside there are two spanners \Njust like these, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.82,0:13:06.09,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, they're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.35,0:13:07.36,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.36,0:13:13.68,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,If you jam both spanners \Ninto the U-shaped spanner
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.68,0:13:19.86,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,of the locked padlock and apply \Nyour weight from above...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.38,0:13:26.74,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.40,0:13:28.83,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.43,0:13:30.36,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.36,0:13:32.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.12,0:13:33.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.88,0:13:37.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,there weren't any marks left on the locker
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.64,0:13:41.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,that would indicate the padlock \Nwas broken using spanners.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.78,0:13:45.92,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Close, Detective, but no cigar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.07,0:13:51.47,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's because after killing Saraie-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.47,0:13:55.93,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,the culprit took the key from his body, \Nunlocked and removed the padlock,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.93,0:13:59.34,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,broke it using the method I just showed you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.34,0:14:02.52,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and then reattached it to the locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.00,0:14:04.93,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,They even ransacked the inside of the locker
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.38,0:14:11.78,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,so it looked like the culprit was after \Nthe contents of Saraie-san's locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.64,0:14:16.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about the contents of the locker?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.01,0:14:18.88,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt anything was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.45,0:14:26.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But those tools aren't \Nenough to swing that vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:30.09,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't need to swing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.50,0:14:31.48,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.48,0:14:36.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.75,0:14:37.86,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.86,0:14:41.19,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Could you get that spanner \Nfrom underneath the drawers?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.38,0:14:42.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.93,0:14:45.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.01,0:14:47.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I have to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.79,0:14:50.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.09,0:14:54.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty far back. I can't reach it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.45,0:14:55.15,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.80,0:15:01.73,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,They forcefully dropped the vase on \Ntop of the victim's head like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.73,0:15:03.25,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.84,0:15:08.25,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,They asked the victim to get something \Nfrom underneath the drawers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.88,0:15:13.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,so they could kill him by simply lifting \Nthe vase instead of swinging it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.44,0:15:16.40,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,After propping the victim up like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.40,0:15:21.14,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,they put the flowers they had in their \Nlocker in the vase, filled it with water,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.58,0:15:24.04,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,and pushed the vase towards \Nthe blood splatter
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.04,0:15:27.83,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,on the floor caused by the impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.25,0:15:30.65,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,This removed the blood splatter,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.33,0:15:33.16,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,while also creating the illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.70,0:15:38.91,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,that the vase had always contained water.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.51,0:15:40.45,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.45,0:15:44.62,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You said you could wrap your \Nwrist in bandages later
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.62,0:15:48.19,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,to make it seem like it \Nwas dislocated all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.19,0:15:49.67,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.76,0:15:52.43,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.43,0:15:54.18,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.45,0:15:56.94,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The trick you just described...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.94,0:15:59.13,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Could've been used by any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.59,0:16:03.94,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.57,0:16:09.17,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.14,0:16:10.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.85,0:16:12.73,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,After all that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.73,0:16:14.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.38,0:16:16.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.24,0:16:23.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You were wearing socks earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.48,0:16:26.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so why aren't you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.66,0:16:27.34,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.78,0:16:32.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You were wearing socks when you picked \Nup the pieces of the glass I broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.29,0:16:35.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you take them off?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.61,0:16:39.32,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm a sweaty person.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.32,0:16:41.50,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,They were drenched in sweat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.21,0:16:44.64,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,They were gross, so I took them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.67,0:16:48.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.03,0:16:50.29,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.29,0:16:51.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.05,0:16:55.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So it's not because you got blood
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.04,0:16:57.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,on your socks when you dropped the vase?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.91,0:17:01.04,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.61,0:17:05.81,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Your shoes and pants are black, \Nso blood isn't visible on them,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.81,0:17:08.92,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,but you were forced to remove your socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.46,0:17:10.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.99,0:17:16.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's something under the drawers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.23,0:17:22.97,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. Is that a pearl earring?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.97,0:17:25.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it's stuck to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:29.53,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.53,0:17:35.99,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,You asked Saraie-san to use the vacuum to \Nsuck up the earring underneath the drawers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.83,0:17:39.24,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,using the narrow hose attachment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.14,0:17:44.77,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,But if it was stuck there with glue, \Nit would've been difficult to get.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.77,0:17:50.00,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,So while he was lying on the floor, \Nyou dropped the vase on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.39,0:17:54.01,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But where did she get all this water?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.85,0:18:04.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, brat?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.91,0:18:08.19,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't this Naomura-san's locker?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.64,0:18:10.00,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.00,0:18:14.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,She divided the water into plastic \Nbottles and hid them in her locker.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.48,0:18:19.95,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,And she could stop the flowers from wilting \Nby putting them in the filled water bottles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.24,0:18:23.99,DCMain,MOTOSU,0000,0000,0000,,But why, Isuzu-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.99,0:18:26.33,DCMain,HASUNUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Why kill Saraie-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.33,0:18:31.43,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,He criticized my family's \Nrestaurant on his blog as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.29,0:18:36.33,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,Though it's gone now since \Nmy parents killed themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.50,0:18:39.34,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,over their debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.58,0:18:40.47,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.44,0:18:49.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So you did do it for revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.97,0:18:53.72,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,No. At first, I had no intention to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.23,0:18:58.36,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,My father fell ill, so my \Nmother was cooking instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.36,0:19:00.91,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that the quality \Nof our dishes had declined.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.32,0:19:08.54,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to get a job here because I heard \Nthe owner of the blog was a waiter here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.04,0:19:13.42,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to give him a piece of my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.21,0:19:17.45,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm the poster girl of a \Nrestaurant you ruined!"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.45,0:19:19.42,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,"Laugh it up!"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.23,0:19:23.93,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,But do you know what he said when he met me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.39,0:19:26.64,DCItalic,SARAIE,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.64,0:19:28.22,DCItalic,SARAIE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you from Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.22,0:19:30.44,DCItalic,SARAIE,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna go out with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.18,0:19:40.78,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,H-He didn't know you were the poster girl?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.78,0:19:44.59,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,No. He wrote on his blog that the \Nquality of the food had dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.04,0:19:48.33,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,He claimed to be disappointed after dining \Nregularly at our restaurant for years.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.13,0:19:53.48,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,But he never ate our restaurant's food!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.48,0:19:56.84,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,He criticized us based only \Non rumors and our image!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.56,0:20:02.82,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't forgive him for that,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.51,0:20:08.60,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,so I dropped a vase on the head of a man who \Ncalled himself "the Stuffed Professor"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.29,0:20:11.51,DCMain,NAOMURA,0000,0000,0000,,with a stomach full of murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.51,0:21:41.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What an awful case.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.12,0:21:44.84,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you shouldn't trust blogs like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.32,0:21:47.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That was amazing, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.58,0:21:50.11,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you noticed her socks.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.55,0:21:52.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.19,0:21:56.12,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you know the moment \Nwe entered the crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.28,0:22:00.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I saw that she wasn't wearing any socks,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.86,0:22:04.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the victim's elbow was dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.77,0:22:07.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought he might have been doing \Nsomething while lying on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.96,0:22:09.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and looked under the drawers
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.76,0:22:13.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and saw the earring stuck to the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.88,0:22:17.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.60,0:22:21.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You can't tell if something's stuck \Nto the floor just by looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.44,0:22:22.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I could tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.62,0:22:31.13,Missing,,0000,0000,0000,,Floor
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.13,0:22:25.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Normally if a pearl earring \Nfell on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.06,0:22:27.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the post would be touching \Nthe floor due to its weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.32,0:22:31.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but the post of that earring \Nwas pointing upwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.28,0:22:38.00,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.26,0:22:40.75,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, you might be a genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.07,0:22:42.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing amazing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.24,0:22:44.05,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.44,0:22:50.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I spent all that time thinking about it, \Nbut I still don't understand your trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.58,0:23:00.02,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, you're so cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.16,0:23:02.89,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He really is a little kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.89,0:23:04.07,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,You stupid little kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.72,0:23:08.73,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I told you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.73,0:23:10.83,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,That trip is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.83,0:23:13.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,...your standard high school...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.72,0:23:15.87,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,...school trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.31,0:23:20.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.79,0:23:22.75,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I gave you the handout.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.08,0:23:25.25,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I totally forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.49,0:23:30.17,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt even Shinichi-kun \Nwould miss this trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.70,0:23:33.73,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You think he'll come?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.73,0:23:35.18,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.88,0:23:37.24,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.31,0:23:39.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.04,0:23:43.26,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I really want to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.77,0:23:51.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But we saw him smoking \Ncigarettes. Right, Ran-neechan?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.23,0:23:55.45,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. From right around here, \Nwhen we gave them our gift.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.84,0:23:59.37,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably safe to assume \Nthere was no foul play.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.59,0:24:05.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's become clear to me that this is a \Nmurder made to look like an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Murderous Carpool
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.71,0:24:13.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan \Nis "The Murderous Carpool!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.91,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Cushion
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.88,0:24:33.14,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.60,0:24:34.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A cushion!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:39.91,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.15,0:24:36.39,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The elementary school's...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.39,0:24:37.50,DCMain,SERA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}...school trip...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.50,0:24:38.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}...isn't for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.65,0:24:39.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Damn it!
